---
Description: Tibetan saying
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 366
    Verse: 8
Tags:
  - Possessions
---
Whatever there be on the surface of the earth -- property, gold, cattle,
good health -- none of these truly satisfy man. Tranquility arises from
this understanding.
